#+title: Analytic Tradition

* Friedrich Ludwig Gottlob Frege
:PROPERTIES:
:ID: 3f543ff8-2f04-4229-b969-da3cee9ac47d
:END:
- *1848 - 1925*
- A German mathematician, logician, and philosopher who worked at the _University of Jena_.
- Founded [[id:4d9986f4-7959-4f35-b04d-c63f166c13df][Analytic Tradition]] in the late *19th century*.
- He essentially reconceived the discipline of [[roam:Logic]] by constructing a formal system which, in effect, constitued the first '/predicate calculus/'.
* Definition
- also claled *linguistic philosophy*.
  + a related set of approaches to philosophical problems.
- Philosophy should apply _logical techniques_ to attain conceptual _clarity_.
